00:36:42.729 --> 00:36:44.520
Some of them did not
go to a French school,

00:36:44.520 --> 00:36:46.936
because that's the problem
that we have usually in Guinea.

00:36:46.936 --> 00:36:49.830
You If you didn't go to a French
school or an English school,

00:36:49.830 --> 00:36:51.330
you are called an
illiterate person.

00:36:51.330 --> 00:36:54.420
Even though you are valuable,
you might know certain things.

00:36:54.420 --> 00:36:56.820
So these people--
ADLaM has been a way

00:36:56.820 --> 00:36:59.880
to bring those
people into the fold.

00:36:59.880 --> 00:37:02.900
Or at least to get them
to share what they know

00:37:02.900 --> 00:37:05.104
or to contribute in
terms of knowledge.

00:37:05.104 --> 00:37:06.270
Because they have knowledge.

00:37:06.270 --> 00:37:08.430
They have things that they
want to do for the community.

00:37:08.430 --> 00:37:10.804
But without them, they could
not have been able to do it.

00:37:10.804 --> 00:37:12.870
And they're the reason
why, actually, ADLaM has

00:37:12.870 --> 00:37:16.410
gotten, because with their--

00:37:16.410 --> 00:37:20.250
with the few means, they don't
have a lot, by whatever they

00:37:20.250 --> 00:37:23.190
have, they invest a lot of
it into ADLaM and trying

00:37:23.190 --> 00:37:24.780
to make it move forward.

00:37:24.780 --> 00:37:27.060
And the first guy that my
brother showed you here

00:37:27.060 --> 00:37:29.393
